      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 37,
      "message": "It is a proxy object for the policy-api, thus PolicyApi makes sense to me.  Don't really like these: \"Controller\" has other connotations in drools-pdp, and \"RestClient\" implies a particular implementation, which the invoker doesn't need to know or care about.\n\nNevertheless, if PolicyApi is not acceptable, then I would probably go with PolicyApiManager; even though it doesn't manage policy-api, it does manage communication with policy-api, and that is often what \"Manager\" means in class names.",
